ational_types.html\">Type</a> u</div></div>","info":{"doc":"A structure that contains the data to uniquely define an ideal sheaf, consisting of\n1. an ideal `I(U) ≤ Γ(X, U)` for every affine open `U`\n2. a proof that `I(D(f)) = I(U)_f` for every affine open `U` and every section `f : Γ(X, U)`\n3. a subset of `X` equal to the support.\n\nAlso see `Scheme.IdealSheafData.mkOfMemSupportIff` for a constructor with the condition on the\nsupport being (usually) easier to prove.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/IdealSheaf/Basic.html#AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData","kind":"structure","line":56,"name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/AlgebraicGeometry/IdealSheaf/Basic.lean#L56-L74"}}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Morphisms.QuasiCompact","Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.Properties","Mathlib.Tactic.DepRewrite"],"instances":[{"className":"PartialOrder","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData.instPartialOrder","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData"]},{"className":"CompleteSemilatticeSup","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData.instCompleteSemilatticeSup","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData"]},{"className":"OrderTop","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData.instOrderTop","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData"]},{"className":"OrderBot","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData.instOrderBot","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData"]},{"className":"SemilatticeInf","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData.instSemilatticeInf","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData"]},{"className":"CompleteLattice","name":"AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData.instCompleteLattice","typeNames":["AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IdealSheafData"]}],"name":"Mathlib.AlgebraicGeometry.IdealSheaf.Basic"}